	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 26th 2:05 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the tip about Harmony cant hurt to try it. Root breaks a lot we all know that. Get lotsa wisdom and kite. I solo yellows in OT I use snare not ensnare it doesnt last as long but uses less mana, after i snare I dot&nbsp;&nbsp;with drones ( im level 35)then Combust and I use careless lightning as my less mana blast in case its resisting a lot  that way i conserve. I never get hit I never kite less than white and only die if a goon gets me which Im always looking for on track. The trick here is to have 2 blasts one with less mana nothing worse than having your 182 dam spell hit for 8 when that happens  go to less mana lightning. Be careful if you take too long you will need to re snare. Its all about Mana Management. Im at 184 wis now, and im not twinked  I just maxed my wis at the start.<br> PS I know A 37 druid with 117 wis who uses AE spell to kite 3 at a time NOW Thats A REAL TRICK! Happy Hunting  :)   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
